This action aims to enable the EU to address short and medium-term foreign policy needs and opportunities and to respond to a dynamic and fast-changing foreign policy environment that the EU has been and remains confronted with.

The Conflict Prevention, Peacebuilding and Crisis Preparedness Support Measures will contribute to the research, identification, formulation, evaluation, and implementation of interventions, inter alia providing technical assistance and training, and organising meetings and seminars, bringing relevant stakeholders together, for actions under the thematic area Peace, Stability and Conflict prevention of the NDICI.
